source: crates/webpkit-cli/tests/snapshot.rs
expression: "dump(\"cwebp\", \"-h\")"
---
$ cwebp -h
cwebp (webpkit) — encode PNG/PPM/PAM to WebP (lossy by default)

Usage: cwebp [options] <input> -o <output.webp>

Options:
  -o <file>              output file (`-` for stdout)
  -q <float>             lossy quality 0-100 (default 75); effort in -lossless mode
  -m <int>               method 0-6 (effort)
  -lossless              encode losslessly (VP8L) instead of lossy (VP8)
  -z <int>               lossless level 0-9 (implies -lossless)
  -near_lossless <int>   near-lossless preprocessing 0-100, lower = stronger (implies -lossless)
  -metadata <list>       all,none,icc,exif,xmp (default: all)
  -preset <name>         content preset: default, photo, picture, drawing, icon, text (a tuning base)
  -crop x y w h          crop before encoding (dimensions match libwebp; pixels differ)
  -resize w h            resize before encoding (0 on one axis keeps aspect)
  -size <int>            target output size in bytes (searches lossy quality)
  -psnr <float>          target reconstruction PSNR floor in dB (lossy)
  -pass <int>            number of entropy-refinement passes 1-10 (1 = single pass)
  -sns <int>             spatial noise shaping 0-100
  -f <int>               in-loop filter strength 0-100
  -sharpness <int>       in-loop filter sharpness 0-7
  -segments <int>        number of quantizer segments 1-4
  -partition_limit <int> first-partition rate cap 0-100 (0 = no limit)
  -jpeg_like             bias quantization toward a JPEG-like size curve
  -sharp_yuv             luminance-guided (sharp) chroma subsampling
  -exact                 preserve the RGB under fully-transparent pixels (the default)
  -alpha_q <int>         alpha quality 0-100 (100 = lossless, the default)
  -alpha_method <int>    alpha compression: 0 raw, 1 lossless (default)
  -alpha_filter <str>    alpha filter: none, fast, or best (default)
  -noalpha               drop the alpha channel (encode opaque)
  -quiet                 suppress the status line
  -short                 concise output: print only the result size
  -progress              report encoding progress by stage
  -v                     verbose output (repeatable)
  -color <when>          auto (default), always, or never
  -version               print version
